01:29.524 --> 01:31.830
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:31.961 --> 01:33.484
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:33.615 --> 01:35.834
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.965 --> 01:37.619
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.749 --> 01:40.448
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.578 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:23.360 --> 02:29.105
♪ THERE COMES A TIME WHEN YOU DECIDE IF
YOU WILL LEAD OR FOLLOW ♪

02:33.457 --> 02:39.333
♪ DON'T WAIT AROUND TILL YOU HAVE FOUND
THAT TIME CANNOT BE BORROWED ♪

02:43.772 --> 02:47.863
♪ WE'RE ALL TRYING HARD TO MAKE IT BUT
SOMETIMES IT'S HARD TO SEE ♪

02:47.993 --> 02:52.998
♪ WHEN WE'RE RUNNING ROUND IN CIRCLES WE
GET SO DIZZY ♪

02:53.129 --> 02:56.872
♪ NOW IT'S TIME TO TAKE THE WHEEL AND MAKE
IT FEEL ♪

02:57.002 --> 03:00.354
♪ LIKE THERE IS NO TOMORROW

03:04.575 --> 03:07.099
-WELL, THE TRADITION CONTINUES.

03:07.230 --> 03:10.146
FIRST NEELY, THEN
DONNA, NOW LANI.

03:10.277 --> 03:12.366
ALL ON THE COVER
OF INSIDE SPORTS.

03:12.496 --> 03:14.150
-YEAH. WELL, PERSONALLY,

03:14.281 --> 03:16.239
I WISH THE TRADITION
ENDED WITH DONNA.

03:17.022 --> 03:18.633
-HOBIE: DUDE, I'D BE
STOKED IF MY GIRLFRIEND

03:18.763 --> 03:21.070
WAS ON THE COVER OF A MAGAZINE.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.419
-CODY: LANI AND I WERE
SUPPOSED TO GO TO CABO

03:22.550 --> 03:23.507
ON OUR VACATION.

03:23.638 --> 03:26.031
NOW HE'S TAKING THEM TO ALASKA.

03:26.902 --> 03:28.686
HOW DO YOU DO A SWIMSUIT
LAYOUT IN ALASKA?

03:28.817 --> 03:30.253
-ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

03:30.384 --> 03:32.299
FIRE AND ICE IS GONNA
BE THE HOTTEST MAG YET.

03:32.429 --> 03:34.649
-MITCH: DO I DETECT A
NOTE OF JEALOUSY, CODY?

03:35.563 --> 03:37.391
-YOU'RE TELLING ME YOU'RE
NOT THE LEAST BIT JEALOUS

03:37.521 --> 03:40.002
THAT NEELY'S CRUISIN' TO
ALASKA ON THE LOVE BOAT?

03:40.132 --> 03:41.612
-MITCH: CONTRARY TO RUMORS,

03:41.743 --> 03:43.614
NEELY AND I ARE JUST FRIENDS.

03:44.659 --> 03:46.530
-MITCH, THE TWO OF YOU
ARE LIVIN' TOGETHER.

03:46.661 --> 03:49.316
-THE FOUR OF US ARE
LIVING TOGETHER TEMPORARILY

03:49.446 --> 03:51.840
TILL NEELY AND ASHLEY
CAN AFFORD A PLACE

03:51.970 --> 03:52.884
OF THEIR OWN.

03:57.454 --> 04:02.851
♪ BUT IF I WORK HARD I CAN PLAY HARD BE A
SUPER STAR ♪

04:07.464 --> 04:12.121
♪ WORD ON THE STREET IS- YOU CAN'T TAKE
THE HEAT ♪

04:12.252 --> 04:17.039
♪ ME AND MY GIRLS WILL MAKE YOUR HEART
SKIP A BEAT ♪

04:17.168 --> 04:19.476
♪ WITH THE SUN ON OUR SIDE

04:19.607 --> 04:22.000
♪ AS WE ROLL WITH THE TIDE

04:22.130 --> 04:24.525
♪ YOU CAN TRY ALL YOU WANT

04:24.655 --> 04:27.267
♪ BUT YOU CAN'T KEEP US FROM OUR FUN

04:27.397 --> 04:29.965
♪ WITH THE SALT ON OUR SKIN

04:30.095 --> 04:32.968
♪ YOU KNOW WE'RE PLAYING TO WIN

04:33.098 --> 04:34.535
-YOU KNOW WHAT WE SHOULD DO?

04:35.275 --> 04:37.320
WE SHOULD GET TICKETS AND
GO ON THE CRUISE WITH THEM.

04:37.886 --> 04:39.627
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO SEE ALASKA.

04:40.323 --> 04:41.498
-CODY,

04:41.629 --> 04:44.632
A RELATIONSHIP IS
BASED ON TRUST.

04:44.762 --> 04:46.634
-CODY: YEAH, I
KNOW ALL ABOUT THAT.

04:46.764 --> 04:47.896
I'M CALLIN' A TRAVEL
AGENT RIGHT NOW.

04:48.026 --> 04:49.376
-DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME.

04:50.072 --> 04:51.029
-WHY? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

04:51.160 --> 04:52.117
-I ALREADY TRIED.

04:53.771 --> 04:56.034
-MITCH: DAWN PRINCESS
IS SOLD OUT.

04:56.644 --> 04:58.385
-CODY: THERE'S ALWAYS
LAST-MINUTE CANCELLATIONS.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.038
-HOBIE: AND THERE'S ALWAYS A
CHANCE I'LL WIN THOSE TICKETS

05:00.169 --> 05:01.866
FROM THAT CONTEST.

05:01.997 --> 05:03.607
-MITCH: WHAT CONTEST?

05:03.738 --> 05:06.044
-THE ONE PRINCESS
CRUISES IS SPONSORING.

05:06.175 --> 05:07.959
YOU REMEMBER THAT AD ON TV.

05:08.090 --> 05:10.440
THEY'RE GONNA ANNOUNCE
THE WINNER ANY DAY NOW.

05:13.748 --> 05:16.359
-ANNOUNCER: FAR TO THE NORTH
OF WHERE YOU AND I DWELL,

05:16.490 --> 05:19.580
THERE LIVES A
BEAUTIFUL PRINCESS.

05:20.102 --> 05:22.147
WIN A DREAM VACATION FOR FOUR

05:22.278 --> 05:25.673
FROM PRINCESS CRUISES
AND ALASKA AIRLINES.

05:26.891 --> 05:29.503
WRITE AN ESSAY IN
200 WORDS OR LESS

05:29.633 --> 05:32.375
EXPLAINING WHY YOU AND
THREE OF YOUR FRIENDS

05:32.506 --> 05:35.770
DESERVE TO CRUISE
ALASKA'S INSIDE PASSAGE

05:35.900 --> 05:37.989
ON THE LOVE BOAT.

05:38.120 --> 05:41.428
HURRY. CONTEST ENDS IN 30 DAYS.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.647
-GIVE ME A BREAK, HOBIE.

05:43.778 --> 05:45.997
WHAT ARE THE ODDS OF YOU
WINNING SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

05:46.694 --> 05:49.392
-BETTER THAN THE ODDS OF
YOU TAKING LANI TO CABO.

05:50.698 --> 05:51.655
-FUNNY

05:59.707 --> 06:01.448
-YOU GOTTA GET
USED TO IT, ASHLEY.

06:02.449 --> 06:03.798
I'M RUNNING FIVE MILES

06:03.928 --> 06:04.842
EVERY MORNING

06:04.973 --> 06:06.366
WHILE YOUR MOM'S GONE.

06:06.496 --> 06:08.629
BY THE TIME SHE GETS
BACK FROM ALASKA

06:08.759 --> 06:10.631
YOU'RE GONNA BE READY
FOR THE TRIATHLON.

06:10.761 --> 06:12.676
-THAT'S SOMETHING WE
NEED TO TALK ABOUT.

06:12.807 --> 06:13.851
-OH, I KNOW, I KNOW.

06:13.982 --> 06:15.462
KEEP HER OUT OF THE SUN,

06:15.592 --> 06:17.028
KEEP PLENTY OF FORMULA,

06:17.159 --> 06:19.640
MAKE SURE THE BRAKE IS
ALWAYS ON WHEN WE STOP,

06:19.770 --> 06:21.511
DON'T FORGET PAMPERS.

06:22.338 --> 06:23.687
WHAT? WHAT'D I FORGET?

06:23.818 --> 06:25.776
-THAT'S NOT WHAT
I WAS GONNA SAY.

06:25.907 --> 06:27.343
-WHAT WERE YOU GONNA SAY?

06:27.474 --> 06:29.563
-WELL, THAT I'LL BE
TAKING ASHLEY WITH ME

06:29.693 --> 06:30.651
ON THE CRUISE.

06:30.781 --> 06:32.043
-WHY?

06:32.653 --> 06:33.610
YOU'RE WORRIED THAT HOBIE
AND I CAN'T TAKE CARE OF HER

06:33.741 --> 06:35.003
WHILE YOU'RE GONE?

06:35.133 --> 06:36.134
-NO, IT'S GOT NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU.

06:36.265 --> 06:38.180
I FINALLY TRACKED DOWN PETER.

06:38.310 --> 06:40.400
HE'S LIVING IN ALASKA.

06:40.530 --> 06:42.619
JUNEAU. IT'S ONE OF THE
STOPS ON THE CRUISE.

06:43.315 --> 06:44.665
-PETER. YOUR EX-HUSBAND, PETER.

06:44.795 --> 06:46.101
-YEAH.

06:46.231 --> 06:47.929
-SO. YOU'RE GONNA
INTRODUCE ASHLEY

06:48.059 --> 06:48.973
TO HER DADDY.

06:50.105 --> 06:51.019
GREAT. GREAT.

06:51.149 --> 06:52.063
HE MUST BE THRILLED.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.326
-WELL, I, UH,

06:54.936 --> 06:55.763
I HAVEN'T TOLD HIM YET.

06:56.677 --> 06:58.026
-YOU HAVEN'T TOLD HIM?

06:58.156 --> 07:00.115
-NO. I MEAN WHAT AM
I SUPPOSED TO SAY?

07:00.245 --> 07:02.857
"HI, IT'S YOUR EX-WIFE,
REMEMBER WHEN WE WERE THINKING

07:02.987 --> 07:04.293
"ABOUT GETTIN' BACK TOGETHER?

07:04.424 --> 07:07.035
"WELL, I GOT PREGNANT.
I HAD A BABY,

07:07.165 --> 07:09.603
"AND, I DIDN'T
BOTHER TO TELL YOU."

07:09.733 --> 07:12.170
THAT'S, UH. THAT'S NOT
THE KIND OF CONVERSATION

07:12.301 --> 07:13.128
YOU HAVE ON THE PHONE.

07:13.911 --> 07:16.261
-YOU'RE JUST GONNA
SHOW UP ON HIS DOORSTEP.

07:16.392 --> 07:18.002
-I DON'T KNOW.

07:18.133 --> 07:19.874
I STILL NEED TO WORK OUT
MY FEELINGS TOWARD PETER.

07:20.004 --> 07:21.397
I MEAN, ON THE ONE HAND,

07:21.528 --> 07:23.791
HE DESERVES TO BE
PART OF ASHLEY'S LIFE.

07:23.921 --> 07:25.401
AND ON THE OTHER HAND,

07:25.532 --> 07:27.751
I DON'T KNOW IF I
WANT HIM TO BE A PART OF MY LIFE.

07:28.578 --> 07:30.754
THEN I THINK THAT SHE DESERVES
TO BE A PART OF A FAMILY,

07:30.885 --> 07:33.583
AND THAT PETER AND I SHOULD
GIVE IT ANOTHER SHOT.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.150
I WISH YOU WERE COMING.

07:35.280 --> 07:37.282
I'M GONNA NEED ALL THE
MORAL SUPPORT I CAN GET.

07:37.413 --> 07:38.893
-COME HERE, COME HERE.

07:41.112 --> 07:42.636
YOU GOT IT, OKAY?

07:43.245 --> 07:44.246
YOU GOT IT.

07:44.376 --> 07:45.508
-OKAY.

07:45.639 --> 07:46.814
-LET'S GO.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.382
-MITCH: THAT'S
IT? YOU FINISHED?

07:50.513 --> 07:52.123
YEAH, YEAH, GOOD, GIRL.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.691
HEY, HEY.

07:55.387 --> 07:56.301
YEAH.

08:00.131 --> 08:02.612
-SO, YOU REALLY THINK
NEELY'S GONNA GET BACK

08:02.743 --> 08:03.831
TOGETHER WITH HER EX?

08:03.961 --> 08:05.485
-THAT'S HARD TO SAY.

08:05.615 --> 08:08.009
HAVING A CHILD IS A STRONG
BOND BETWEEN TWO PEOPLE.

08:08.139 --> 08:09.271
-WASN'T STRONG ENOUGH

08:09.401 --> 08:10.838
TO KEEP YOU AND MOM TOGETHER.

08:10.968 --> 08:12.274
-THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

08:12.404 --> 08:14.102
-WELL, MAYBE IT'S
NOT STRONG ENOUGH

08:14.232 --> 08:16.017
TO GET NEELY AND
WHAT'S-HIS-NAME BACK TOGETHER.

08:16.147 --> 08:17.497
-PETER.
-WHAT?

08:17.627 --> 08:19.281
-HIS NAME IS PETER.

08:19.411 --> 08:21.501
-ALL I KNOW IS THAT
YOU'RE THE ONLY REAL FATHER

08:21.631 --> 08:23.459
ASHLEY'S EVER HAD,

08:23.590 --> 08:25.417
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE
NOT GONNA PUT UP A FIGHT TO KEEP HER.

08:27.594 --> 08:28.812
-IT'S NOT MY CHOICE.

08:28.943 --> 08:30.510
OR YOUR CHOICE.

08:31.989 --> 08:33.600
OR EVEN LITTLE ASHLEY'S CHOICE.

08:33.730 --> 08:36.167
LOOK. LET'S JUST NOT
TALK ABOUT IT, OKAY?

08:36.298 --> 08:37.299
[KNOCK ON THE DOOR]

08:37.429 --> 08:38.386
-HERE.

08:39.126 --> 08:40.041
BURP HER WILL YOU?

08:40.171 --> 08:41.390
-YEAH.
-OKAY.

08:41.912 --> 08:43.087
YEAH.

08:45.699 --> 08:47.135
-MITCH: HEY.
-HEY.

08:47.265 --> 08:48.353
YOU GUYS EAT YET?

08:48.484 --> 08:49.964
-MITCH: NO, COME ON IN. I'M STARVED.

08:50.094 --> 08:51.618
YEAH, I KNEW YOU
WERE WATCHING ASHLEY,

08:51.748 --> 08:54.011
AND I FIGURED YOU
MIGHT BE HUNGRY.

08:54.577 --> 08:55.926
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE

08:56.057 --> 08:58.363
AT SOME INSIDE SPORTS
DINNER WITH LANI.

08:58.494 --> 08:59.800
-YEAH, WELL, THAT WAS BEFORE

08:59.930 --> 09:01.279
LANI AND I GOT IN A HUGE FIGHT

09:01.410 --> 09:02.324
AND SHE SAID SHE NEVER
WANTED TO SEE ME AGAIN.

09:02.454 --> 09:03.455
-OH.

09:03.586 --> 09:05.109
-WE NEED TO HAVE A LONG TALK.

09:05.240 --> 09:06.981
YOU'RE BLOWIN' THIS
WAY OUT OF PROPORTION.

09:07.111 --> 09:08.286
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

09:08.417 --> 09:09.592
MY TURN.

09:14.292 --> 09:15.424
HEY, HOW'S IT GOIN'?

09:15.555 --> 09:16.381
-DELIVERY MAN: PRETTY GOOD.

09:16.512 --> 09:17.426
-I KNOW I'M NUTS BUT

09:17.557 --> 09:19.123
ALL I CAN THINK OF IS CJ.

09:19.254 --> 09:20.385
REMEMBER SHE WAS SUPPOSED
TO GO AWAY FOR A WEEK

09:20.516 --> 09:21.517
AND SHE NEVER CAME BACK?

09:21.648 --> 09:22.605
-LIGHTEN UP, MAN.

09:22.736 --> 09:23.563
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN WITH LANI.

09:23.693 --> 09:24.868
-THANKS A LOT.

09:27.305 --> 09:28.219
OVERNIGHT MAIL.

09:28.350 --> 09:30.091
-FROM WHO?

09:31.483 --> 09:33.181
-PRINCESS CRUISES.

09:33.311 --> 09:35.009
-THE CONTEST.

09:35.139 --> 09:36.097
YOU SAID THEY WERE GONNA
ANNOUNCE THE WINNERS. WHAT'S IT SAY?

09:36.227 --> 09:37.620
-CONGRATULATIONS.

09:37.751 --> 09:39.753
YOU'RE THE WINNER OF
THE PRINCESS CRUISES

09:39.883 --> 09:41.450
ALASKA AIRLINES SWEEPSTAKES.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.104
I'M GOIN' TO ALASKA!
-CODY: YES!

09:43.234 --> 09:44.758
-HEY, WHOA, UNBELIEVABLE.

09:44.888 --> 09:45.889
LOOK AT THIS.

09:46.411 --> 09:47.761
-YOU GUYS MISSED
THE ESSAY I WROTE.

09:47.891 --> 09:49.197
I WROTE ABOUT HOW
MUCH I LOVED THE BEACH

09:49.327 --> 09:50.938
AND HOW BAD WE
NEEDED A VACATION.

09:51.068 --> 09:52.417
-YOU ARE THE MAN.

09:52.548 --> 09:53.505
-MAJESTIC MOUNTAINS,
WONDROUS STREAMS,

09:53.636 --> 09:54.550
INCREDIBLE GLACIERS, FISHING.

09:54.681 --> 09:55.507
AWE, MAN. THIS IS AWESOME.

09:55.638 --> 09:57.074
-YEAH!
-YES.

09:57.205 --> 09:58.685
-NOW ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS FIND THREE PEOPLE

09:58.815 --> 09:59.903
TO GO WITH ME.

10:00.034 --> 10:00.904
SO I'M TAKIN' BIDS.

10:01.035 --> 10:02.689
-WELL, I'M YOUR FATHER.

10:02.819 --> 10:04.473
FATHER.

10:04.604 --> 10:05.343
-TWENTY BUCKS AND I'LL DO
YOUR LAUNDRY FOR A MONTH.

10:05.474 --> 10:06.649
-YEAH, YEAH.

10:06.780 --> 10:07.911
-YOU GOT TWENTY
BUCKS FOR ME, DAD?

10:08.042 --> 10:08.956
-NO, BUT I'M YOUR FATHER.
-DEAL?

10:09.086 --> 10:10.044
DEAL.

10:10.174 --> 10:10.871
-ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE GOIN'.

10:11.001 --> 10:12.002
-YEAH!

10:23.840 --> 10:28.018
[DARK, OMINOUS PIANO MUSIC]

12:40.063 --> 12:42.544
-OH MY GOD, WOULD YOU
LOOK AT THESE THINGS?

12:42.674 --> 12:44.198
THESE GOTTA BE WORTH A FORTUNE.

12:44.328 --> 12:45.199
-OH, THEY ARE.

12:46.200 --> 12:47.636
WE CAN CUT THOUSANDS OF STONES

12:47.767 --> 12:49.420
FROM JUST ONE OF THESE EMERALDS.

12:49.551 --> 12:52.075
NOW, WHAT ARE WE GETTIN'
OUT OF THIS, ROBBY? HUH?

12:52.206 --> 12:54.512
WE RISKED OUR LIVES
DIVING FOR THESE.

12:54.643 --> 12:56.036
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

12:56.166 --> 12:57.472
-I'M TALKING ABOUT
GETTING OUR FAIR SHARE

12:57.602 --> 12:59.082
OF THE PROFITS.
-WHAT?

12:59.213 --> 13:01.128
ARE YOU OUTTA YOUR MIND, LESLIE?

13:01.911 --> 13:03.130
YOU FORGETTIN' WHO WE'RE
DEALIN' WITH, HERE?

13:03.260 --> 13:04.653
LOOK, THESE GUYS ARE KILLERS.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.220
YOU'D NEVER MAKE
IT OFF THE DOCK.

13:06.350 --> 13:07.482
THEY KILLED TO GET
THESE EMERALDS.

13:07.612 --> 13:08.526
THEY'LL KILL TO KEEP 'EM.

13:09.440 --> 13:10.877
-YOU GUTLESS WORM.

13:11.007 --> 13:12.443
-SHUT UP, LESLIE.

13:12.574 --> 13:14.054
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.

13:14.184 --> 13:15.969
-ALL I KNOW IS I AM TIRED
OF WORKING FOR NOTHING.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.622
-YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?

13:17.753 --> 13:19.407
I THINK YOU MIGHTA STAYED
DOWN A LITTLE TOO LONG.

13:19.537 --> 13:21.496
YOU'RE NOT THINKIN' STRAIGHT.

13:23.324 --> 13:25.500
-YOU'RE THROWIN' AWAY
THE CHANCE OF A LIFETIME.

13:25.630 --> 13:26.675
-NO. YOU KNOW WHAT I'M DOIN'?

13:26.806 --> 13:28.155
I'M PLAYIN' IT SMART.

13:28.285 --> 13:29.634
ALL RIGHT? I SUGGEST
YOU DO THAT SAME.

13:31.201 --> 13:32.159
NOW WHY DON'T YOU COME HELP ME

13:32.289 --> 13:33.160
WITH THIS ANCHOR?

13:59.839 --> 14:01.014
-COME GIVE ME A
HAND WITH THIS THING.

14:01.144 --> 14:02.102
I WANT TO GET OUTTA HERE.

14:06.106 --> 14:07.107
[MAN GRUNTS]

14:33.220 --> 14:35.352
[MAN YELLS]

14:56.896 --> 15:01.726
[MAN YELLS]

15:04.860 --> 15:06.122
-NO!

15:19.353 --> 15:20.963
-BYE-BYE, BABY.

16:02.265 --> 16:03.266
-APRIL: HEY, NEWMIE!

16:03.397 --> 16:04.876
-NEWMIE: YEE-HAH!

16:06.356 --> 16:07.662
HERE I COME.

16:10.099 --> 16:11.144
-WOO!

16:11.274 --> 16:12.841
-APRIL: THIS IS SO FUN.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.277
-YEE-HAH!

16:20.980 --> 16:22.198
-HEY, NEWMIE.

16:22.329 --> 16:23.678
-WOO-HOO!

16:49.182 --> 16:50.226
-IT'S ME.

16:50.748 --> 16:52.185
I'VE GOT THE EMERALDS.

16:53.360 --> 16:55.188
NO, QUINN IS ON THE
BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN

16:55.318 --> 16:56.624
SUCKING ON AN ANCHOR.

16:57.364 --> 16:58.713
YEAH. NO, OF COURSE.
[PLAYFUL SHOUTS FROM SKIERS]

16:58.843 --> 17:00.193
OF COURSE I WAS CAREFUL.

17:00.323 --> 17:02.499
LOOK, I KNOW WHAT
THEY WOULD DO TO ME

17:02.630 --> 17:04.066
IF I GOT CAUGHT.

17:04.196 --> 17:05.936
WHICH IS WHY I'M NOT
GOING TO GET CAUGHT.

17:06.068 --> 17:08.810
NOW, YEAH, I SAW THEM ONCE.

17:08.940 --> 17:11.377
NO, NO THEY WON'T REMEMBER.

17:12.378 --> 17:14.642
BESIDES, EVEN IF THEY DO,

17:15.164 --> 17:18.079
THEY'LL BE SEARCHING FOR
A BLONDE LESLIE STRYKER.

17:18.602 --> 17:20.169
I'M CLAIR HODGES NOW.

17:20.300 --> 17:22.084
I'M A REDHEAD.

17:23.303 --> 17:24.260
-NEWMAN: ALL RIGHT, APRIL.

17:24.391 --> 17:26.045
LOOKING GOOD.

17:28.482 --> 17:30.092
-STOP THE BOAT.

17:35.880 --> 17:37.143
-SHERYL: APRIL'S DOWN.

17:37.273 --> 17:38.361
-JIM: OKAY. LET'S PICK HER UP.

18:03.865 --> 18:04.953
-HOLD ON.

18:10.785 --> 18:11.742
NO.

18:12.352 --> 18:13.962
WE MAY HAVE A PROBLEM HERE.

18:18.619 --> 18:19.489
-SHERYL, NO!

18:19.620 --> 18:21.143
THERE'S A SHARK.

18:32.111 --> 18:33.634
LETS GET HIM BACK TO THE SCARAB.

18:35.418 --> 18:38.508
[HARD BREATHING]

18:44.253 --> 18:46.037
-I CAN'T TELL IF
HE'S DEAD OR ALIVE.

18:50.346 --> 18:51.521
-EASY.

19:02.010 --> 19:04.055
[MAN YELLS]

19:14.370 --> 19:16.111
-BARNETT, I GOT YA COVERED.

19:18.983 --> 19:20.420
-NEWMAN: HELP 'EM IN THE BOAT.

19:43.094 --> 19:44.313
-LOOK, ENOUGH. OKAY?

19:44.444 --> 19:45.923
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

19:59.023 --> 20:00.938
JUST WAIT UNTIL I CALL YOU

20:01.069 --> 20:03.245
AND TELL YOU WHERE TO MEET ME.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.210
-RADIO THE COAST GUARD.
WE'RE GONNA NEED A HELICOPTER.

20:11.340 --> 20:12.689
-NEWMIE, THEY WON'T
MAKE IT IN TIME.

20:12.820 --> 20:14.430
-GET THE AMBU BAG.

20:14.561 --> 20:15.475
-BARNETT: THERE'LL
BE AN AMBULANCE WAITING AT THE DOCK.

20:15.605 --> 20:16.780
-HE HAS SEVERE HEAD TRAUMA.

20:16.911 --> 20:18.173
-WHAT DO YOU THINK
HAPPENED TO HIM?

20:18.304 --> 20:19.696
-PROBABLY FELL OFF SOME BOAT.

20:22.264 --> 20:24.614
-ONE, TWO THREE.

20:32.840 --> 20:35.016
-APRIL: NO ONE SEEMS
TO BE LOOKING FOR HIM.

20:36.365 --> 20:39.020
-NEWMAN: ONE, TWO, THREE

20:39.150 --> 20:41.022
FOUR, FIVE.

21:22.455 --> 21:25.501
[POLICE AND AMBULANCE SIRENS]

21:26.285 --> 21:28.112
-CLAIR: THAT BASTARD
BETTER NOT BE ALIVE.

21:45.216 --> 21:46.305
-DOCK WORKER: GOT IT.

22:08.762 --> 22:09.719
-CLAIR: THIS
DORK SHOULD GET ME

22:09.850 --> 22:11.025
INTO LIFEGUARD HEADQUARTERS.

23:03.947 --> 23:04.992
-HOBIE: WHAT'S SHE DOING?

23:05.645 --> 23:06.820
WATCH OUT!

23:06.950 --> 23:08.387
[WOMAN YELLS]

23:09.823 --> 23:10.737
-CLAIR: HELP!

23:15.829 --> 23:16.786
HELP!

23:16.917 --> 23:19.789
SOMEBODY, PLEASE HELP ME.

23:19.920 --> 23:21.138
HELP.

23:38.460 --> 23:39.374
-ARE YOU OKAY?

23:39.505 --> 23:40.984
-I'M NOT SURE.

23:41.507 --> 23:42.943
-HOLD ON TO THIS.
-OKAY.

23:43.073 --> 23:44.597
-I'LL TOW YOU IN.
-OKAY.

23:48.644 --> 23:50.472
-ARE YOU DOING ALL
RIGHT BACK THERE?

23:51.038 --> 23:52.082
-I'M FINE.

24:07.750 --> 24:09.360
[PHONE RINGING]

24:12.538 --> 24:13.887
-HI, HOBIE.
-WHAT'S UP?

24:14.888 --> 24:16.716
-HEY, CLAIR. SORRY
ABOUT THE WAIT.

24:17.630 --> 24:18.457
THANKS A LOT, AL.

24:18.587 --> 24:19.501
-UH, HUH.

24:21.460 --> 24:23.374
-SO, I'M GONNA HAVE TO ASK YOU

24:23.505 --> 24:24.680
A COUPLE QUESTIONS.

24:24.811 --> 24:26.203
-ABOUT WHAT?

24:26.334 --> 24:27.640
-WELL, WHEN A LIFEGUARD
PARTICIPATES IN A RESCUE

24:27.770 --> 24:29.293
HE HAS TO TAKE
AN INCIDENT REPORT.

24:29.424 --> 24:30.860
REAL BASIC STUFF. COME ON.

24:35.822 --> 24:36.649
SIT RIGHT HERE.

24:36.779 --> 24:37.780
-THANKS.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.745
-SO, HAVE YOU EVER
BEEN IN A KAYAK BEFORE?

24:45.875 --> 24:48.574
-THE FUNNY THING
IS, I ROW EVERY DAY.

24:48.704 --> 24:49.966
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

24:50.097 --> 24:51.794
IT'S AS IF MY BRAIN
JUST SHUT DOWN

24:51.925 --> 24:53.753
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN
HERE'S THIS BOAT COMING

24:53.883 --> 24:55.058
STRAIGHT AT ME.

24:55.581 --> 24:57.365
THANK GOODNESS YOU
WERE THERE, HOBIE.

24:57.496 --> 24:58.497
IT WAS THE SCARIEST THING

24:58.627 --> 25:00.281
THAT HAS EVER HAPPENED TO ME.

25:00.411 --> 25:01.412
FEEL MY HAND.

25:01.543 --> 25:02.979
I'M STILL SHAKING.

25:03.110 --> 25:04.198
-OH, DON'T WORRY.

25:04.328 --> 25:05.504
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

25:08.245 --> 25:09.116
-WHAT'S UP, HOBE?

25:09.246 --> 25:10.509
-HEY, WHAT'S UP, JD.?

25:10.639 --> 25:12.336
-HOW'S IT GOING?
-HOBIE: GOOD.

25:12.467 --> 25:13.816
-CONGRATULATIONS.

25:13.947 --> 25:15.209
I HEARD ABOUT YOU
CRUISIN' TO ALASKA.

25:15.339 --> 25:16.732
-HOBIE: HEY [SHUSHES]

25:16.863 --> 25:18.255
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
A SECRET, ALL RIGHT?

25:18.386 --> 25:19.692
-HEY, I HAVEN'T SAID A WORD.
-ALL RIGHT.

25:19.822 --> 25:21.258
-SO, GOT A SPOT OPEN?

25:21.389 --> 25:22.738
-UM, POSSIBLY.

25:22.869 --> 25:23.870
HEY, I'LL TALK TO
YOU ABOUT IT LATER.

25:24.000 --> 25:25.132
-YEAH, SURE.

25:25.262 --> 25:26.307
DON'T FORGET ABOUT ME.

25:26.437 --> 25:27.656
-I WON'T.
-WHO LOVES YA?

25:27.787 --> 25:29.092
-LOVE YA, BABE.
-ALL RIGHT.

25:31.051 --> 25:33.444
-AH, SO, BACK TO
THE INCIDENT REPORT.

25:33.575 --> 25:35.403
NAME, CLAIR HODGES.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.884
IS THAT A C-L-A-I-R-E?

25:38.014 --> 25:38.972
-UH, NO E.

25:39.102 --> 25:40.190
-ALL RIGHT.

25:40.843 --> 25:43.324
-SO, UH, YOU'RE GOING
ON A CRUISE TO ALASKA?

25:43.454 --> 25:45.326
-YEAH, I WON THIS CONTEST AND--

25:45.456 --> 25:46.849
-WHEN ARE YOU GOING?

25:46.980 --> 25:49.286
-ACTUALLY, WE LEAVE
FOR VANCOUVER TOMORROW.

25:49.417 --> 25:50.723
-OH.

25:50.853 --> 25:52.246
GUESS WE WON'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHANCE

25:52.376 --> 25:54.378
TO SPEND ANY TIME TOGETHER.

25:54.509 --> 25:55.684
BUT THAT'S OKAY.

25:55.815 --> 25:56.816
YOU ARE GONNA HAVE
A FABULOUS TIME

25:56.946 --> 25:58.252
IN ALASKA.

25:58.382 --> 25:59.253
IT IS SO GORGEOUS
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

25:59.383 --> 26:00.341
-YOU'VE BEEN THERE?

26:00.471 --> 26:01.342
-I LIVE THERE.

26:01.472 --> 26:03.518
WELL, I USED TO.

26:03.649 --> 26:04.867
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

26:04.998 --> 26:06.869
-I CAME DOWN HERE
TO DO RESEARCH

26:07.000 --> 26:08.044
ON WHALE MIGRATION.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.742
I'M MAJORING IN MARINE BIOLOGY.

26:09.872 --> 26:13.223
ANYWAY, THE APARTMENT
I WAS STAYING IN,

26:13.354 --> 26:14.311
IT GOT RIPPED OFF.

26:14.442 --> 26:15.617
THEY TOOK EVERYTHING.

26:15.748 --> 26:17.706
ALL MY CLOTHES,
MY TUITION MONEY.

26:17.837 --> 26:19.316
IT'S ALL GONE.

26:20.361 --> 26:21.754
-OH, THAT'S TERRIBLE.

26:21.884 --> 26:23.494
WHAT ABOUT YOUR PARENTS?
CAN'T THEY HELP YOU OUT?

26:24.757 --> 26:26.933
-MY PARENTS WERE KILLED
IN AN ACCIDENT LAST YEAR.

26:27.629 --> 26:29.413
SO WERE MY BROTHER AND SISTER.

26:30.632 --> 26:31.502
-I'M SORRY.

26:32.373 --> 26:33.853
-THERE'S NOTHING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT.

26:35.681 --> 26:37.204
-WELL, MAYBE THERE IS.

26:37.726 --> 26:38.988
I'VE GOT FOUR TICKETS.

26:39.119 --> 26:41.121
SO FAR, IT'S ME,
MY DAD, AND CODY.

26:41.904 --> 26:43.558
YOU COULD BE THE FOURTH.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.168
-HOBIE, YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ME.

26:45.299 --> 26:47.344
-I KNOW, BUT I FEEL LIKE I DO.

26:47.475 --> 26:48.607
-YOU DO?

26:49.608 --> 26:50.609
THAT'S SO SWEET.

26:52.132 --> 26:53.916
I FEEL THAT WAY ABOUT YOU TOO.

26:55.178 --> 26:56.658
BUT I COULDN'T.

26:56.789 --> 26:57.616
I COULDN'T IMPOSE.

26:57.746 --> 26:59.095
-OH, COME ON, WHY NOT?

26:59.226 --> 27:01.924
IT'D BE LIKE I WAS
GIVING YOU A RIDE HOME.

27:02.055 --> 27:03.709
-REALLY?
-YEAH.

27:04.797 --> 27:06.625
-THIS IS SO INCREDIBLE.

27:06.755 --> 27:08.539
NO ONE HAS EVER DONE
ANYTHING LIKE THIS FOR ME.

27:08.670 --> 27:11.586
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN MY
WHOLE LIFE, HOBIE BUCHANNON?

27:12.282 --> 27:13.675
-I BEEN RIGHT HERE.

27:14.371 --> 27:15.546
-THANK YOU.
-NO PROBLEM.

27:17.200 --> 27:18.419
-IS THERE SOMEWHERE
I CAN CHANGE?

27:18.549 --> 27:19.899
-UH, YEAH. GIRLS LOCKER ROOM.

27:20.029 --> 27:21.074
DOWN THE STAIRS.

27:21.204 --> 27:22.118
LET'S GO.

27:22.684 --> 27:23.685
-HEY GUYS.

27:23.816 --> 27:25.034
WHAT WAS THAT CODE R ALL ABOUT?

27:25.165 --> 27:26.470
I THOUGHT YOU WENT WATER SKIING.

27:26.601 --> 27:27.907
-WELL, WE WERE UNTIL APRIL

27:28.037 --> 27:28.821
FOUND A BODY FLOATING
IN THE WATER.

27:28.951 --> 27:30.300
-JD.: OH MY GOD.

27:30.431 --> 27:31.824
-YEAH, WE THOUGHT
HE WAS DEAD AT FIRST

27:31.954 --> 27:34.043
BUT WE GAVE HIM CPR
AND HE'S STILL ALIVE.

27:34.174 --> 27:35.784
-NEWMAN: WE DON'T KNOW IF
HE'S GONNA PULL THROUGH THOUGH.

27:35.915 --> 27:37.090
HE WAS STILL IN A COMA WHEN
WE GOT HIM TO THE SHORE.

27:37.699 --> 27:39.440
-I'M GONNA CALL THE HOSPITAL
AND SEE HOW HE'S DOING.

27:39.570 --> 27:40.615
THEY TOOK HIM TO
PACIFICA MEDICAL, RIGHT?

27:40.746 --> 27:41.616
-RIGHT.
-ALL RIGHT.

27:41.747 --> 27:43.400
-JD.: OH, MAN.

27:48.275 --> 27:49.319
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

27:49.450 --> 27:50.451
-WHAT HAPPENED?

27:50.581 --> 27:51.582
-YOU PASSED OUT.

27:51.713 --> 27:52.888
-I DID?

27:53.019 --> 27:55.282
OH, ALL I REMEMBER
IS GETTING DIZZY

27:55.412 --> 27:56.979
AND FEELING NAUSEOUS.

27:57.893 --> 27:59.329
THIS IS GETTING REALLY WEIRD.

27:59.852 --> 28:01.114
-WE BETTER GET YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL.

28:01.723 --> 28:02.681
-I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:02.811 --> 28:03.943
-COME ON.

28:10.384 --> 28:11.690
-OH, THERE YOU ARE.

28:11.820 --> 28:13.430
JUST FINISHED
EXAMINING YOUR VICTIM.

28:13.561 --> 28:14.823
VITAL SIGNS ARE NORMAL.

28:14.954 --> 28:16.172
NO SALT WATER IN THE LUNGS.

28:16.303 --> 28:17.826
NO EVIDENCE OF
INTERNAL INJURIES.

28:17.957 --> 28:19.262
YOU KNOW, I SUSPECT
THE DIZZINESS

28:19.393 --> 28:20.873
WAS MORE A RESULT
OF NERVOUS TENSION

28:21.003 --> 28:22.701
THAN PHYSICAL TRAUMA.

28:22.831 --> 28:25.573
SEEMS TO BE UNDER AN
INORDINATE AMOUNT OF STRESS.

28:25.704 --> 28:27.140
-SEE, I JUST MET HER,

28:27.270 --> 28:28.663
SO I DON'T REALLY KNOW
THAT MUCH ABOUT HER.

28:28.794 --> 28:30.012
-WELL.

28:30.143 --> 28:31.622
SHE'LL BE OUT IN
A MOMENT OR TWO.

28:31.753 --> 28:33.189
SHE'S BEING RELEASED
AS WE SPEAK.

28:33.320 --> 28:35.452
-DO YOU KNOW IF ANYBODY'S
COMING TO PICK HER UP?

28:36.236 --> 28:38.020
-I DON'T THINK
SHE'S GOT ANY FAMILY

28:38.151 --> 28:39.500
IN THE LOS ANGELES AREA.

28:39.630 --> 28:41.067
-OKAY. I'LL TAKE HER HOME.

28:41.981 --> 28:43.591
-I HOPE SHE
APPRECIATES HOW MUCH

28:43.722 --> 28:44.505
YOU'VE DONE FOR HER.

28:44.635 --> 28:46.550
-ME TOO.
-OKAY.

28:46.681 --> 28:48.248
-THANKS.
-YOU BET.

29:03.524 --> 29:04.743
-WHERE IS QUINN?

29:05.482 --> 29:07.006
-PACIFICA TRAUMA CENTER

29:07.136 --> 29:08.398
IN CRITICAL CONDITION.

29:09.051 --> 29:11.271
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-I DON'T KNOW.

29:11.401 --> 29:13.403
BUT I HAVE A FEELING
WE'VE BEEN DOUBLE-CROSSED.

29:13.534 --> 29:15.188
-YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT
FIVE MILLION DOLLARS

29:15.318 --> 29:16.363
IN EMERALDS.

29:16.493 --> 29:17.407
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO REMIND ME.

29:17.538 --> 29:19.018
-WHERE THE HELL IS LESLIE?

29:19.148 --> 29:20.236
-I DON'T KNOW.

29:20.367 --> 29:21.716
BUT I'M GONNA FIND OUT.

29:21.847 --> 29:23.762
PACIFICA TRAUMA CENTER.
LET'S MOVE IT.

29:38.559 --> 29:39.734
-INCREASE HIS OXYGEN

29:39.865 --> 29:41.780
AND CHECK HIM AGAIN
IN 15 MINUTES.

30:02.191 --> 30:06.108
[HOSPITAL MACHINERY BEEPS]

30:07.936 --> 30:10.417
-YOU'RE TOUGHER THAN
I THOUGHT, ROBBY, BABY.

30:11.592 --> 30:13.246
BUT NOT TOUGH ENOUGH.

30:14.203 --> 30:16.989
YOU SHOULD'VE LISTENED
TO ME, YOU BASTARD.

30:17.119 --> 30:18.686
GREED IS GOOD.

30:19.556 --> 30:21.950
SO WHILE YOU'RE ROTTING IN HELL,

30:22.081 --> 30:24.823
IT'LL JUST BE ME
AND THE EMERALDS

30:24.953 --> 30:27.477
CRUISING ON THE DAWN
PRINCESS IN ALASKA.

30:27.608 --> 30:29.828
PRETTY CLASSY GETAWAY, HUH?

30:35.572 --> 30:37.052
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY.

30:37.618 --> 30:38.967
WHERE THERE'S A WILL,

30:39.098 --> 30:41.056
THERE'S A WAY.

30:41.187 --> 30:42.884
BYE-BYE, BABY.

30:44.625 --> 30:45.669
[HOSPITAL CURTAIN ZIPS BACK]

30:47.280 --> 30:48.890
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

30:49.021 --> 30:50.979
-UM, WELL, I WAS WALKING PAST

30:51.110 --> 30:52.546
AND I HEARD HIM MOAN.

30:52.676 --> 30:54.069
-WELL, THIS IS
A RESTRICTED AREA.

30:54.200 --> 30:55.679
-I'M SORRY.

30:55.810 --> 30:57.203
I SHOULD HAVE CALLED A NURSE.
-THAT'S OKAY.

30:57.333 --> 30:58.508
NO HARM, NO FOUL.

30:59.814 --> 31:01.555
-WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?
-NOBODY KNOWS.

31:02.730 --> 31:04.384
HE WAS FOUND
FLOATING IN THE OCEAN

31:04.514 --> 31:05.820
BY THE LIFEGUARDS.

31:05.951 --> 31:07.474
-IS HE GONNA DIE?

31:07.604 --> 31:09.955
-WELL, IT DEPENDS ON HOW
LONG HE REMAINS IN A COMA.

31:10.085 --> 31:13.306
BUT IF YOU HEARD HIM MOANING,
HE COULD BE COMING TO.

31:14.350 --> 31:16.004
LET'S, UH, STEP OUTSIDE.

31:20.400 --> 31:21.575
GOOD AS NEW.

31:22.141 --> 31:23.142
-ALL RIGHT. THANKS, DOC.

31:23.272 --> 31:24.317
-YOU BE CAREFUL OUT THERE NOW.

31:24.447 --> 31:25.231
-I WILL.
-OKAY.

31:25.361 --> 31:26.232
BYE.
-THANKS

31:26.754 --> 31:28.103
-YOU FEEL BETTER NOW?

31:28.234 --> 31:30.149
-ACTUALLY, I FEEL
A LITTLE FOOLISH.

31:30.279 --> 31:31.672
YOU KNOW, FOR OVERREACTING.

31:31.802 --> 31:33.630
SUCH A MAJOR HYPOCHONDRIAC.

31:33.761 --> 31:34.762
-OH, YEAH. DON'T
WORRY ABOUT IT.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.285
BETTER SAFE THAN SORRY.

31:36.416 --> 31:37.852
I MEAN, YOU DON'T
WANT TO GET OUT TO SEA

31:37.983 --> 31:38.897
AND FIND OUT SOMETHING'S
WRONG WITH YOU, RIGHT?

31:39.027 --> 31:40.246
-THAT'S TRUE.

31:40.376 --> 31:41.334
LET'S GO.

31:43.597 --> 31:44.728
-EXCUSE ME.

31:46.469 --> 31:47.296
EXCUSE ME, DOCTOR?

31:47.427 --> 31:48.819
-WHAT'S WRONG?

31:48.950 --> 31:50.212
-I UNDERSTAND YOU
HAVE A DROWNING VICTIM

31:50.343 --> 31:51.387
IN INTENSIVE CARE.

31:51.518 --> 31:52.606
-AND YOU ARE?

31:52.736 --> 31:53.520
-HIS BROTHER.

31:53.650 --> 31:55.522
-HUH? UM, NOTHING.

31:55.652 --> 31:56.915
NOTHING. I WAS GETTING EXCITED

31:57.045 --> 31:58.003
THINKING ABOUT OUR TRIP.

31:58.133 --> 31:59.178
-ME TOO.

32:05.358 --> 32:06.750
-I WISH I COULD
BE MORE OPTIMISTIC

32:06.881 --> 32:08.970
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER'S
CHANCES OF RECOVERY.

32:09.101 --> 32:11.277
THE TRUTH IS, HE'S
LUCKY TO BE ALIVE.

32:11.842 --> 32:13.540
LIFEGUARDS FOUND HIM
IN THE NICK OF TIME.

32:13.670 --> 32:14.671
-DO YOU THINK I COULD HAVE

32:14.802 --> 32:16.021
A MOMENT ALONE WITH HIM, DOC?

32:16.804 --> 32:18.197
-SURE. I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

32:18.893 --> 32:20.721
I HAVE TO MAKE MY ROUNDS ANYWAY.

32:21.330 --> 32:22.505
IF YOU NEED ANY ASSISTANCE

32:22.636 --> 32:23.854
JUST ASK THE NURSE.

32:23.985 --> 32:25.508
-THANK YOU.
-NO PROBLEM.

32:33.734 --> 32:34.865
-WAY TO GO, ROBBY,

32:34.996 --> 32:36.955
YOU INCOMPETENT JACKASS.

32:37.085 --> 32:38.695
I TOLD YOU SHE
COULDN'T BE TRUSTED,

32:38.826 --> 32:40.219
BUT YOU KNEW BETTER.

32:43.091 --> 32:45.311
WELL, LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING, SMART GUY.

32:45.441 --> 32:47.139
WE DON'T GET THOSE
EMERALDS BACK,

32:47.269 --> 32:48.792
YOU'RE GONNA WISH
THOSE LIFEGUARDS

32:48.923 --> 32:50.272
NEVER FOUND YOU.

32:51.317 --> 32:53.362
[MAN IN COMA MUMBLES]

32:53.493 --> 32:54.711
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

32:56.148 --> 32:57.236
-EMERALDS.

32:58.019 --> 32:59.107
LESLIE.

32:59.760 --> 33:01.936
DAWN PRINCESS.

33:02.545 --> 33:03.982
ALASKA.

33:12.816 --> 33:14.253
-ORDERLY: HOLD ON,
I'LL GET THE DOOR.

33:19.780 --> 33:20.737
-GO.

33:21.347 --> 33:22.913
THAT BITCH HAS THE EMERALDS.

33:23.044 --> 33:23.958
-WHERE THE HELL IS SHE?

33:24.611 --> 33:26.265
-ON SOME CRUISE SHIP,

33:26.395 --> 33:27.222
THE DAWN PRINCESS,

33:27.353 --> 33:28.528
ON HER WAY TO ALASKA.

33:28.658 --> 33:29.877
-YOU REMEMBER WHAT
SHE LOOKS LIKE?

33:30.008 --> 33:31.052
-HOW WOULD I REMEMBER?

33:31.183 --> 33:32.401
WE NEVER MET?
-YOU DID.

33:32.532 --> 33:34.229
AT A PARTY I HOSTED A MONTH AGO.

33:34.360 --> 33:37.058
MID-TWENTIES, BROWN
EYES, BLONDE HAIR.

33:37.189 --> 33:38.581
PERFECT GIRL-NEXT-DOOR.

33:38.712 --> 33:40.670
-YEAH, IF YOU LIVE NEXT
DOOR TO SAN QUENTIN.

33:40.801 --> 33:43.021
-LISTEN, I WANT
THOSE EMERALDS BACK.

33:43.151 --> 33:44.544
YOU HEAR ME?

33:44.674 --> 33:45.675
AND I DON'T CARE WHAT
YOU DO TO GET 'EM.

33:45.806 --> 33:46.807
AND BY THE WAY,

33:46.937 --> 33:47.895
I DON'T EVER WANT TO SEE

33:48.026 --> 33:49.679
MISS LESLIE STRYKER AGAIN. EVER.

33:49.810 --> 33:51.681
-I GUARANTEE YOU SHE
WILL NEVER GET OFF

33:51.812 --> 33:53.335
THAT CRUISE SHIP ALIVE.

34:04.477 --> 34:06.305
-MAN, THIS SHIP
IS AWESOME LOOKING.

34:06.435 --> 34:07.610
HEY, SO YOU THINK WE'RE
REALLY GONNA BE ABLE TO

34:07.741 --> 34:09.221
SURPRISE THE GIRLS?

34:09.351 --> 34:10.351
EVERYBODY AT HEADQUARTERS
KNOWS WE'RE GOING.

34:10.483 --> 34:12.527
-LANI AND DONNA ARE OFF TODAY.

34:12.659 --> 34:13.920
SO UNLESS NEELY FOUND OUT,

34:14.052 --> 34:15.487
WE ARE IN THE CLEAR.

34:15.618 --> 34:17.098
HERE'S THE PLAN.

34:17.228 --> 34:18.969
FIRST, THEY FLY TO
VANCOUVER IN THE MORNING.

34:19.100 --> 34:20.667
WE TAKE THE AFTERNOON FLIGHT,

34:20.797 --> 34:23.061
AND WE ARE IN ALASKA.

34:23.190 --> 34:24.409
-HEY, SO WHO ELSE IS GOING?

34:24.540 --> 34:25.802
-I DON'T KNOW.

34:25.933 --> 34:26.760
HOBE'S JUST STILL
FIELDING OFFERS.

34:26.889 --> 34:28.152
HEY, HOBE-STER.

34:28.283 --> 34:29.415
-HEY, GUYS.

34:29.545 --> 34:30.938
SOMEONE I WANT YOU TO MEET.

34:31.938 --> 34:34.114
CLAIR HODGES, THIS IS MY DAD.

34:34.246 --> 34:35.333
-HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.

34:35.464 --> 34:36.291
-HI.
-THIS IS CODY MADISON.

34:36.422 --> 34:37.945
-HI.

34:38.076 --> 34:39.773
YOU SHOULD BE SO PROUD
OF YOUR SON, MR. BUCHANNON.

34:39.902 --> 34:41.949
HE SAVED MY LIFE TODAY.

34:42.558 --> 34:43.820
-HE DID?

34:44.473 --> 34:45.953
-I HAVEN'T FINISHED FILLING
OUT THE INCIDENT REPORT YET.

34:46.083 --> 34:47.433
-OH.

34:47.563 --> 34:49.261
-MY KAYAK FLIPPED IN THE MARINA

34:49.391 --> 34:51.089
AND I ALMOST GOT HIT BY A BOAT.

34:51.219 --> 34:53.134
FORTUNATELY, HOBIE WAS
THERE TO RESCUE ME.

34:53.264 --> 34:54.527
-HM.

34:55.179 --> 34:57.182
-UM, CAN YOU TELL ME
WHERE THE BATHROOM IS?

34:57.312 --> 34:59.445
-IT'S UPSTAIRS. FIRST
DOOR ON THE LEFT.

34:59.575 --> 35:00.620
-GREAT. THANKS.

35:00.750 --> 35:02.100
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

35:05.277 --> 35:06.060
-CODY: NOT BAD, HOBIE.

35:06.191 --> 35:07.192
-YEAH.

35:07.888 --> 35:08.758
-HOW OLD IS SHE?

35:09.542 --> 35:10.456
-SHE'S 20.

35:10.586 --> 35:11.979
-20. YEAH, RIGHT.

35:12.893 --> 35:14.547
-HEY, THAT'S WHAT SHE TOLD ME.

35:14.677 --> 35:17.071
YOU ALWAYS SAID NEVER ASK
A WOMAN HER AGE, RIGHT?

35:18.464 --> 35:19.856
-SO YOU GUYS
GOIN' OUT OR WHAT?

35:19.987 --> 35:22.032
-ACTUALLY, I'M GONNA
TAKE HER ON THE CRUISE.

35:22.990 --> 35:24.339
-WHAT?

35:24.470 --> 35:26.124
YOU'RE GONNA TAKE
A GIRL YOU JUST MET

35:26.254 --> 35:27.864
ON AN EIGHT-DAY ALASKAN CRUISE.

35:27.995 --> 35:29.257
-SHE LIVES IN ANCHORAGE.

35:29.388 --> 35:30.867
WE'RE GONNA LEAVE HER UP THERE.

35:30.998 --> 35:32.173
-HOBIE, YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT THIS GIRL.

35:32.304 --> 35:33.783
-WELL, MAYBE I
WANT TO FIND OUT.

35:33.914 --> 35:34.741
SHE'S A NICE GIRL.

35:34.871 --> 35:36.351
I WANT TO HELP HER OUT.

35:37.613 --> 35:39.702
-I'M AWARE THAT THEY'LL
HAVE PEOPLE WATCHING

35:39.833 --> 35:41.878
THE TRAIN STATIONS
AND THE AIRPORTS.

35:42.009 --> 35:44.577
THAT'S WHY I'M TRAVELING
BY CRUISE SHIP.

35:46.100 --> 35:48.450
I THOUGHT IT WAS RATHER
INGENIOUS MYSELF.

35:49.321 --> 35:50.496
BUT QUITE HONESTLY,

35:50.626 --> 35:52.280
THIS IS THE EASIEST CON JOB

35:52.411 --> 35:53.673
I HAVE EVER PULLED.

35:53.803 --> 35:55.022
-HEY, I WON THE CONTEST, RIGHT?

35:55.153 --> 35:56.502
I CAN TAKE WHOEVER I WANT.

35:56.632 --> 35:57.590
-YEAH, YOU CAN TAKE
WHOEVER YOU WANT.

35:57.720 --> 35:58.504
I JUST DON'T WANT YOU TAKING

35:58.634 --> 36:00.288
A TOTAL STRANGER.

36:00.419 --> 36:01.463
-YOU KNOW WHAT?
I DON'T REALLY CARE
WHAT YOU THINK.

36:01.594 --> 36:02.812
I'M 18 YEARS OLD.

36:02.943 --> 36:04.379
YOU CAN'T CONTROL WHO I DATE.

36:04.510 --> 36:05.511
-IT'S MORE THAN A DATE.

36:05.641 --> 36:06.903
-WE HAVE SEPARATE ROOMS.

36:07.034 --> 36:07.991
-THAT'S NOT THE ISSUE.

36:08.122 --> 36:09.210
-WHAT IS THE ISSUE?

36:09.341 --> 36:10.124
YOU WANT HER FOR YOURSELF?

36:10.255 --> 36:11.778
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN'--

36:12.822 --> 36:14.607
-COME ON. WE'RE OUTTA HERE.

36:14.737 --> 36:15.999
-WHY, WHAT'S GOING ON? WHERE'RE WE GOING?
-MITCH: HOBIE.

36:16.130 --> 36:17.349
-WHEREVER.

36:17.479 --> 36:18.524
-HOBIE.

36:19.916 --> 36:21.048
-MITCH: DAMN IT.

36:28.316 --> 36:29.578
-THANK YOU.

36:29.709 --> 36:30.579
-THANK YOU.

36:30.710 --> 36:32.102
-THANKS.

36:32.233 --> 36:33.713
-WELL, WE'RE OFF ON
OUR BIG ADVENTURE.

36:33.843 --> 36:35.236
-ALL RIGHT, ASHLEY,
YOU TAKE CARE OF YOUR MOM.

36:35.367 --> 36:36.890
KEEP EACH OTHER WARM AT NIGHT.

36:37.020 --> 36:38.674
-I'LL CALL YOU FROM
JUNEAU AFTER I SEE PETER.

36:38.805 --> 36:40.067
-WHATEVER.

36:40.198 --> 36:43.113
-HEY, MITCH. NO
MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

36:43.244 --> 36:45.768
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR ALL THAT YOU'VE DONE.

36:45.899 --> 36:47.988
I KNOW WE'VE BEEN
A BIG IMPOSITION.

36:48.118 --> 36:50.120
-YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
AN IMPOSITION.

36:50.251 --> 36:53.950
NEELY, YOU MADE
US A FAMILY AGAIN.

36:54.473 --> 36:55.648
NOW STOP WORRYING.

36:55.778 --> 36:56.649
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

36:56.779 --> 36:58.216
BYE MUFFIN.

36:59.739 --> 37:01.219
-BYE.
-I'LL SEE YOU BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

37:01.349 --> 37:02.611
-OKAY.
-SEE YA.

37:02.742 --> 37:03.482
-WE STILL HAVE
TIME TO MAKE A QUICK

37:03.612 --> 37:05.005
PHONE CALL, RIGHT?

37:05.135 --> 37:06.659
-I THOUGHT YOU AND
CODY WEREN'T TALKING.

37:06.789 --> 37:07.616
-I STILL THOUGHT HE'D COME

37:07.747 --> 37:09.139
AND SAY GOOD-BYE.

37:09.270 --> 37:10.706
I MEAN WE ALWAYS MAKE
UP AFTER A FIGHT.

37:10.837 --> 37:12.708
SOMETIMES THAT'S THE
ONLY REASON WE FIGHT,

37:12.839 --> 37:14.188
JUST TO MAKE UP.

37:14.319 --> 37:15.972
-LANI, WE'RE
GOIN' ON THE LOVE BOAT,

37:16.103 --> 37:18.236
I'M SURE YOU'LL FIND
SOMEONE ELSE TO FIGHT WITH.

37:18.366 --> 37:20.020
HEY, COME ON.
THEY'RE READY TO TAKE OFF.

37:20.150 --> 37:20.934
-HEY, SEE YA.

37:21.064 --> 37:22.414
HAVE FUN.

37:22.544 --> 37:25.155
DON'T EAT TOO MUCH
OF THAT GOURMET CUISINE.

37:28.985 --> 37:30.291
-LOOK, LANI, HOW MANY CHANCES

37:30.422 --> 37:31.684
DO YOU GET TO GO TO ALASKA?

37:31.814 --> 37:32.902
LET'S GO HAVE SOME FUN!

37:33.033 --> 37:34.643
-ALL RIGHT. COME ON.
-OKAY.

37:53.140 --> 37:55.055
-ASHLEY'S FIRST FLIGHT, HUH?

37:55.664 --> 37:57.187
-WELCOME TO ALASKA AIRLINES.

37:57.318 --> 37:58.406
IF THERE'S ANYTHING YOU NEED

37:58.537 --> 37:59.538
MY NAME IS KAT.

37:59.668 --> 38:00.930
WOULD YOU LIKE CHAMPAGNE?

38:01.061 --> 38:01.931
-THAT'S SOUNDS GOOD.
-YEAH, ME TOO.

38:02.062 --> 38:03.281
-YOU KNOW WHAT?

38:03.411 --> 38:04.151
I'M GONNA HAVE SOME CLUB SODA.

38:04.282 --> 38:05.674
-OF COURSE.
-THANKS.

38:05.805 --> 38:07.285
-HEY THERE, LITTLE GIRL.

38:07.415 --> 38:08.460
-SHE'S SLEEPING
-SHE DOING GOOD?

38:08.590 --> 38:09.983
-YEAH.
-SO CUTE.

38:10.723 --> 38:11.767
-OH, YUM.

38:13.595 --> 38:14.857
THANK YOU.

38:18.731 --> 38:20.210
-YES, THANK YOU.

38:21.037 --> 38:22.082
-THANKS, KAT.

38:22.212 --> 38:23.431
-YOU'RE WELCOME.
-EXCUSE ME,

38:23.562 --> 38:24.867
HOW LONG IS
THE FLIGHT TO VANCOUVER?

38:24.998 --> 38:26.869
-IT'S NONSTOP, SO
UNDER THREE HOURS.

38:27.000 --> 38:29.394
-COULD YOU TELL THE PILOT
TO SPEED IT UP A LITTLE?

38:29.524 --> 38:30.873
CAN'T WAIT TO GET ON
THE DAWN PRINCESS.

38:31.004 --> 38:32.440
-I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

38:33.354 --> 38:35.051
-HEY GUYS, I'M SO EXCITED.

38:35.182 --> 38:36.966
I'VE NEVER FLOWN
FIRST-CLASS BEFORE.

38:37.097 --> 38:38.446
-GET USED TO IT.

38:38.577 --> 38:39.708
CAUSE THIS TRIP'S
FIRST-CLASS ALL THE WAY.

38:39.839 --> 38:40.753
-ALL THE WAY.

38:40.883 --> 38:42.537
-I'D LIKE TO MAKE A TOAST.

38:42.668 --> 38:45.018
TO INSIDE SPORTS AND ALASKA.

38:47.063 --> 38:48.761
-ALASKA, HERE WE COME.

